# Svelte 5

- **Props:** `$props()` + typed `Props`; one-line destructure + defaults; **`$bindable()`** when parent binds.
- **State:** `$state` / `$derived` / `$derived.by` ‚Äî not legacy `let` + `$:` for app state.
- **Effects:** `$effect` is an [escape hatch](https://svelte.dev/docs/svelte/$effect#When-not-to-use-$effect) ‚Äî DOM/canvas/third-party/imperative side work; return teardown; don‚Äôt use effects to **sync** one reactive from another (prefer `$derived` / `$derived.by`, handlers, [function bindings](https://svelte.dev/docs/svelte/bind#Function-bindings)). Full audit workflow: **`/audit-svelte-effects`** ‚Üí `.cursor/commands/audit-svelte-effects.md`.
- **Events:** callback props (`onSelect`, ‚Ä¶), not `createEventDispatcher`; `onclick`/`oninput` not `on:click` on components.
- **Snippets:** Svelte 5 snippets; **`Snippet` / `Snippet<[T]>`** args when typed.
- **Structure:** PascalCase components; **`script ‚Üí markup ‚Üí style`**. Prefer **`src/lib/components/ui/`** primitives over one-off styled tags.
- **Canvas:** vanilla TS + `bind:this`; `$effect` to sync DOM; no 60fps churn through runes/store.
- **Styles:** colocated `<style>`; tokens per **css-standards**.
- **`svelte-ignore a11y_*`:** only real false positives; comment why.

Runes live in `.svelte` / `.svelte.ts` / `.svelte.js`; shared stores as `.svelte.ts`; parent‚Üíchild via props/`$derived`, not extra stores.

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  interface Props { count: number; label?: string }
  let { count, label = 'Count' }: Props = $props()
  const doubled = $derived(count * 2)
</script>
```
